56
00:03:34,997 --> 00:04:00,294
Also on suspension, 2011-727 off by Councilor Marks, be resolved that the Mayor McGlynn appointed Citizens Transportation Advisory Committee to establish a new transportation policy and planning framework to include a parking management plan, a traffic flow study, bicyclist-friendly master plan, transportation needs, and to develop a long-term plan to improve pedestrian safety features like crosswalks, signage, and lights.

57
00:04:00,975 --> 00:04:01,475
Councilor Marks.

58
00:04:02,956 --> 00:04:03,917
Thank you, Mr. President.

59
00:04:04,830 --> 00:04:18,642
Uh, the purpose of this resolution tonight, uh, is to create a transportation advisory committee, uh, with volunteer citizens who shall act as a clearing house for transportation issues affecting the city of method.

60
00:04:19,422 --> 00:04:32,533
The committee should provide input and advisory direction to boards and commissions and city administration to assist in suggesting creative ways to deal with the myriad of traffic, pedestrian safety issues, transit service,

61
00:04:32,993 --> 00:04:37,516
and transportation planning issues in the city of method responsibilities.

62
00:04:37,756 --> 00:04:48,583
I perceive this committee to have Mr. President is to review and provide comments and recommendations on a longterm plan to improve pedestrian safety within our community.

63
00:04:49,324 --> 00:05:01,552
Also to review city bus ridership, bus routes every six months and make appropriate recommendations to the council review and provide recommendations on transportation policies, issues and programs,

64
00:05:01,894 --> 00:05:04,995
which involved the MBTA and the commuter rail.

65
00:05:05,875 --> 00:05:10,217
Review and advise on citywide parking management plan and traffic flow.

66
00:05:10,857 --> 00:05:14,479
Review and provide recommendations on a citywide bicycle plan.

67
00:05:15,399 --> 00:05:18,360
Establish an annual work plan to address specific issues.

68
00:05:19,188 --> 00:05:29,140
You know, the town of Arlington has had a Transportation Advisory Commission, which they refer to as TAC, in place for several years now.

69
00:05:29,801 --> 00:05:37,670
And the city of Newton has had this same advisory committee in place, manned with volunteers throughout the community.

70
00:05:38,426 --> 00:05:46,035
And they are not to replace current traffic commissions, boards, authority of anyone in the city.

71
00:05:46,516 --> 00:05:54,445
It's to act in an advisory capacity to assist in moving issues forward that deal with pedestrian safety.

72
00:05:55,455 --> 00:05:59,357
deal with transportation issues in the community, traffic flow.

73
00:05:59,757 --> 00:06:05,280
These are the issues that we hear week after week, month after month, year after year within our community.

74
00:06:06,000 --> 00:06:14,045
And we as a community can no longer afford to sit back and wait for accidents to happen on our street and then react.

75
00:06:15,125 --> 00:06:16,666
We can no longer afford to do that.

76
00:06:17,186 --> 00:06:18,987
We need to take back our streets.

77
00:06:20,588 --> 00:06:22,169
Our streets have become raceways.

78
00:06:23,735 --> 00:06:30,859
They're no longer a place safe for children, seniors, families to walk down our sidewalks or cross the street.

79
00:06:33,001 --> 00:06:35,222
We as a community have to get serious about this.

80
00:06:36,523 --> 00:06:49,571
And one way I believe we can do this is not to react on every street that comes before us or every issue that comes before us, but to have a board, an advisory committee, whatever you want to call it,

81
00:06:50,485 --> 00:07:00,928
that is there to address issues, to do research, to offer opinions, to hold meetings, to get community input, and to follow through on issues.

82
00:07:01,488 --> 00:07:07,750
One of the biggest concerns I have in this community is the lack of follow through.

83
00:07:09,430 --> 00:07:11,971
And it's not just the administration, it's this council.

84
00:07:13,551 --> 00:07:15,512
We need to follow through on issues.

85
00:07:16,385 --> 00:07:20,446
You know, we had the residents of Golden Ave that came up before us several months ago.

86
00:07:21,566 --> 00:07:27,828
I'm still getting emails from those residents that were concerned about heavy trucking and speeding on their street.

87
00:07:29,229 --> 00:07:33,950
Nothing has been done to date to improve the conditions on Golden Ave.

88
00:07:36,150 --> 00:07:38,771
This is symptomatic throughout the entire community.

89
00:07:41,732 --> 00:07:45,513
We need, Mr. President, to tap upon

90
00:07:46,088 --> 00:07:48,590
the many involved citizens in this community.

91
00:07:49,911 --> 00:07:56,336
We can no longer say that this is being handled by the traffic commission, or this is being handled by off-street parking.

92
00:07:57,176 --> 00:08:07,884
We need to get people that want to be involved in this community, want to offer their expertise, their life experience, and involve them in committees.

93
00:08:10,446 --> 00:08:11,747
Residents want to get active.

94
00:08:11,767 --> 00:08:13,328
They want to know how they can help out.

95
00:08:13,669 --> 00:08:15,310
I've already had several emails

96
00:08:16,679 --> 00:08:22,761
from residents of this community stating, Mike, if I can get on this committee, please mention my name.

97
00:08:23,101 --> 00:08:23,881
I'd be interested.

98
00:08:25,381 --> 00:08:26,041
Unsolicited.

99
00:08:27,022 --> 00:08:28,782
People want to get involved.

100
00:08:29,082 --> 00:08:31,263
People want to know how they can help out their community.

101
00:08:33,303 --> 00:08:36,604
There's no salary attached with this citizen advisory board.

102
00:08:36,884 --> 00:08:40,065
It won't cost the city a penny to establish this.

103
00:08:42,163 --> 00:08:57,553
And I'm hoping the mayor sees fit in his capacity as the chief executive officer to create a committee, not just to serve for a year and then dissolve or two years and dissolve, but to be established lifelong committee in this community.

104
00:08:58,033 --> 00:09:06,999
Transportation, although the forms may change and the type of transportation, there'll always be a need to oversee transportation within our community.

105
00:09:08,120 --> 00:09:09,261
There will always be a need.

106
00:09:10,260 --> 00:09:16,305
to make sure pedestrian safety is at the forefront of every issue.

107
00:09:17,927 --> 00:09:32,120
There will always be a need to make sure that our streets are safe, that the T's are accessible, that the current routes work, that the Green Line extension, whatever the capacity may be,

108
00:09:33,902 --> 00:09:35,603
It's going to be beneficial for our community.

109
00:09:36,224 --> 00:09:44,149
These are the things I envision this volunteer committee to work on and make recommendations and they will have a yearly agenda.

110
00:09:44,609 --> 00:09:46,430
This won't be behind closed doors.

111
00:09:46,951 --> 00:09:48,832
This won't be operated in a vacuum.

112
00:09:49,692 --> 00:09:57,217
These will be meetings held by committee posted by the city clerk and attended by residents of this community.

113
00:10:00,720 --> 00:10:00,940
You know,

114
00:10:02,728 --> 00:10:13,296
I talked to one of the town administrators over in Arlington and they said, honestly, they don't know where they would be without this advisory committee.

115
00:10:15,057 --> 00:10:31,689
That's how involved, how influential and how active this committee is in pushing issues forward and doing the research and offering the framework that needs to be done in order to get the plans.

116
00:10:34,365 --> 00:10:39,989
You know, these are the issues that need to be looked at, and we can't afford to address them one at a time.

117
00:10:41,110 --> 00:10:43,392
What street comes up that doesn't have resident permit parking?

118
00:10:44,132 --> 00:10:50,457
The unfortunate accident on Winthrop Street where a student was hit, and now we have painted crosswalks and signage.

119
00:10:52,558 --> 00:10:56,361
No, we can't afford to operate a city no longer like this, Mr. President.

120
00:10:56,711 --> 00:11:02,535
I know there's a resident that came up, there was several residents that emailed me that said they couldn't make it tonight, but we're in full support.

121
00:11:02,555 --> 00:11:05,537
I believe they sent the entire council the email also.

122
00:11:05,798 --> 00:11:14,444
They're in full support of this and I'm hoping, Mr. President, that the mayor sees fit, that it's time that we move this community forward.

123
00:11:14,784 --> 00:11:16,825
We start addressing the transportation issues.

124
00:11:16,845 --> 00:11:18,727
You know, we're five minutes from Boston.

125
00:11:19,067 --> 00:11:24,531
We have all sorts of commuter rail access, T access into town and it's about time

126
00:11:26,557 --> 00:11:28,317
that we take this issue by the horns.

127
00:11:30,158 --> 00:11:31,978
And it's about time we take our streets back.

128
00:11:33,679 --> 00:11:48,442
And I don't want to hear from families that they're afraid to send their kids out because of the speeding on their street, or they're afraid to send them to the square because of the traffic and the cars and the lack of enforcement.

129
00:11:50,662 --> 00:11:51,482
Thank you, Mr. President.

130
00:11:52,002 --> 00:11:52,343
Thank you.

