153
00:13:04,348 --> 00:13:05,228
They came forward.

154
00:13:05,608 --> 00:13:09,369
We were able to push the resolutions forward.

155
00:13:09,389 --> 00:13:13,410
And I think because of us, it got done quicker than it may have gotten done.

156
00:13:13,790 --> 00:13:16,010
But it was a reactive situation.

157
00:13:16,050 --> 00:13:17,651
I think we need to be more proactive.

158
00:13:17,691 --> 00:13:21,792
We need to, what Councilman Marks alluded to,

159
00:13:22,832 --> 00:13:33,514
go through the city and really map out a master plan on how we can improve upon the speeding, the traffic, the accidents, and a whole host of different issues.

160
00:13:33,974 --> 00:13:52,338
My one concern, Council Box, and the rest of the council would be the fact that you sat on a committee for over a year and discussed traffic with the chief of police, you went to other, you know, the committee went to other communities, you come up with this lengthy report on what is needed in the city,

161
00:13:52,832 --> 00:13:54,172
and it just fell on deaf ears.

162
00:13:54,893 --> 00:13:55,613
It went nowhere.

163
00:13:55,733 --> 00:14:03,575
So I would hate to see residents of our community sit and give up their time to not be heard.

164
00:14:03,715 --> 00:14:10,616
So my hope would be not only to implement this committee, but to take the recommendations seriously and to act upon them.

165
00:14:11,497 --> 00:14:17,158
Some of the things that will need to be acted upon are going to cost some money, but at the same time I hope the administration

166
00:14:17,844 --> 00:14:22,528
And I know this council will be committed to improving on what is going on in our community now.

167
00:14:22,648 --> 00:14:24,069
So that would be my concern.

168
00:14:24,089 --> 00:14:29,633
And I hope the administration would not act as they did with the traffic commission report.

169
00:14:30,254 --> 00:14:37,620
Um, my last comment is, you know, the people serving on our traffic commission, they do a good job, they're working hard, but they also have full time jobs.

170
00:14:37,640 --> 00:14:44,245
We're talking the chief of police, Lauren D Lorenzo from the office community development, Jack Buckley from the DPW yards.

171
00:14:45,263 --> 00:14:46,584
from the DBW director.

172
00:14:46,804 --> 00:14:55,787
Those are three people work too many hours to being, you know, to really get into the nitty gritty of what a traffic committee would be able to do.

173
00:14:55,907 --> 00:15:05,451
So I'm in favor and I hope that it not only moves forward, but that the recommendations and the time put into resolves are acted upon.

174
00:15:05,471 --> 00:15:07,212
Thank you.

175
00:15:07,472 --> 00:15:08,232
Councilor Camuso.

176
00:15:08,891 --> 00:15:12,372
Thank you, Mr. President, and I applaud Counselor Marks for bringing this forward.

177
00:15:12,392 --> 00:15:21,656
I think now more than ever, Mr. President, this is something that would be a good addition to the boards and commissions that we have that look at some of these issues.

178
00:15:22,256 --> 00:15:32,280
As we know, statutorily, under mass general laws, certain boards and commissions have the statutory obligation to act or not act on these because it falls under their jurisdiction.

179
00:15:32,760 --> 00:15:37,282
With that being said, though, having more citizen input, other than just having them attend the

180
00:15:38,522 --> 00:15:44,865
regular business meetings of the boards that are tasked with putting some of these into place, I think is great.

181
00:15:45,305 --> 00:15:48,606
And now more than ever, Mr. President, there's more vehicles on the road.

182
00:15:49,287 --> 00:15:54,569
And quite frankly, I think this may be a good time for the mayor to look at all the boards and commissions.

183
00:15:54,989 --> 00:15:56,189
throughout the entire city.

184
00:15:56,890 --> 00:15:59,251
Maybe some of them are not needed anymore.

185
00:15:59,571 --> 00:16:05,393
Maybe new ones are needed, maybe more in technology area or other areas.

186
00:16:05,793 --> 00:16:24,280
So at the same time, if Councillor Marks wouldn't mind, actually make it a B paper because I certainly, I understand the importance of his proposal before us to maybe take a look at all the boards and commissions and see if it's an appropriate time, Mr. President, to either add

187
00:16:24,727 --> 00:16:31,130
combine or delete some of the commissions or boards based upon, um, uh, just today's day and age.

188
00:16:32,110 --> 00:16:33,991
And we have many fine members that are on these boards.

189
00:16:34,511 --> 00:16:43,235
And, uh, if the, uh, board is no longer needed, maybe they're willing to serve in another capacity, uh, where their professionalism will be recognized and, uh, help this community move forward.

190
00:16:43,736 --> 00:16:46,097
But, uh, thank you, councilor marks for bringing this forward.

191
00:16:47,417 --> 00:16:47,697
Thank you.

192
00:16:47,997 --> 00:16:48,918
Vice president Del Rosso.

193
00:16:49,518 --> 00:16:53,640
Uh, mr. President, uh, through the chair to council marks, thank you for your, uh,

194
00:16:54,410 --> 00:16:55,911
You're moving this.

195
00:16:56,872 --> 00:17:07,219
I think I have over the years mentioned in one way or another that what we have doesn't work all that well most of the time.

196
00:17:07,239 --> 00:17:10,081
I'm grateful for the people that serve on those boards and commissions.

197
00:17:10,661 --> 00:17:13,223
But there's some things not working in this community.

198
00:17:13,763 --> 00:17:23,369
I know a lot of it boils down to money that we're not able to implement and do the things that a lot of people have the vision to see done.

199
00:17:25,302 --> 00:17:27,084
This is a worthy step.

200
00:17:27,164 --> 00:17:34,831
I wonder if, I just wonder out loud, I don't have the answer to it, if it adds another layer to government that might become cumbersome.

201
00:17:35,932 --> 00:17:37,693
So the whole thing needs to be looked at.

202
00:17:38,774 --> 00:17:51,806
The other point that Councilor Lungo-Kern had brought up so aptly is that sometimes one is left with the feeling that these boards

203
00:17:52,410 --> 00:18:14,208
that have great participation, which is what you envision, Counselor, great participation, talent from the community, insight, vision, forward thinking, oftentimes they end up in stagnation in an action because of whatever reasons not being theirs.

204
00:18:15,149 --> 00:18:21,514
And I wouldn't want to see something so grand as this to be diminished.

205
00:18:22,345 --> 00:18:24,367
and to have people's hopes dashed.

206
00:18:25,548 --> 00:18:27,349
I don't know what the answer is.

207
00:18:27,429 --> 00:18:28,690
This is a worthy start.

208
00:18:30,652 --> 00:18:34,975
What we have and what we're doing in this community isn't working.

